100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 2, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, where discussions centered on disarmament and peacekeeping efforts amidst growing tensions in Europe. In the United States, the Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of the National Industrial Recovery Act, a key component of President Coolidge's economic strategy. Meanwhile, the British Parliament debated the implications of recent unrest in Ireland, highlighting ongoing challenges in the region.
